BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:trad-overview-2026@daksh-fitness-journey
DTSTAMP:20260611T120000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260621
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260622
SUMMARY:Traditional 5-day split overview
DESCRIPTION:Classic 5-day body-part split. Train Monday to Friday\, rest Saturday and Sunday. Runs 21 June to 28 December. No day has more than 6 exercises. Abs are added on the lower-volume days (chest\, back\, shoulders).\n\nWEEK STRUCTURE\nMon: Chest\nTue: Back\nWed: Shoulders\nThu: Arms\nFri: Legs\nSat & Sun: Rest\n\nCHEST (+ abs)\n1. Incline smith machine press\n2. Flat dumbbell bench press\n3. Decline bench press\n4. Pec deck fly\n5. Cable crossover\n6. Abs superset: leg raises, cable crunches, hip raises\n\nBACK (+ abs)\n1. Deadlifts\n2. Wide-grip lat pulldown\n3. T-bar rows\n4. Seated cable rows\n5. Shrugs\n6. Abs superset: leg raises, cable crunches, hip raises\n\nSHOULDERS (+ abs)\n1. Seated shoulder press\n2. Dumbbell lateral raises\n3. Cable lateral raises\n4. Rear delts on pec deck fly\n5. Face pulls\n6. Abs superset: leg raises, cable crunches, hip raises\n\nARMS\n1. Preacher curls\n2. Incline dumbbell curls\n3. Hammer curls\n4. Straight bar tricep pushdown\n5. Skull crushers\n6. Overhead tricep extension\n\nLEGS\n1. Squats\n2. Leg press\n3. Leg extension\n4. Hamstring curls\n5. Romanian deadlifts\n6. Standing calf raises
END:VEVENT
